Nudged by @craftylumberjacks to make these plaid cuties for the play area at my parents house. So cutie!

Inspired by @craftylumberjacks - here’s my takeaway… My biggest tips with this project: start with a 12x12 and 6x6 SQUARE paper packs (like from Michael’s or hobby lobby) slow down, take the time to perfectly match your corners and make crisp folds. Use fishing line or clear thread to hang them. And I like to make an assembly line for myself when I have a lot of steps and a high volume. For example, I make the same single fold on all the sheets. Then I make the second single fold on all the sheets. Then the hot dog fold, then the hamburger fold, and on and on. For my brain I have to do it like this or I get overwhelmed. Anyone else like that?

Christmas things! Been thinking about my bestie, imagining him with me while I’ve been hunting down holiday moments this month. Here are a few things you should go do:
1. Ice Skating at the Galleria. Or at least park and go inside to admire one of the largest indoor Christmas trees! Totally worth it. 

2. Sit in the lobby of @theadolphushotel  and just vibe. We do this every single year and this year is no exception. Their three story tall tree is REAL. whenever i come here i feel like I’m transported right back to the Art Deco era and it is 🫰🏼🫰🏼🫰🏼.

3. That gorgeous life-sized nativity is in front of the @parkcitiesbaptistchurch . It is so stunning I had to flip my car around and go back to see it up close. Beautiful. 

4. The glorious Santa house address is 3625 Southwestern Blvd in dallas. This is actually a great starting point if you’re interested in seeing the dallas mansions all festive! 

5. The 12 Days of Christmas neighborhood - type in Timberhollow Cir in dallas and it will take you right to it. 

That’s all for now!

is your sign to go line dancing! I put on my fringe-y boots, took my galpal with me to a free line dance lesson in Dallas, and learned a fun new line dance! You couldn’t have slapped my cheese-eatin’ grin off my face. I grew up doing all the line dances and two-steppin and tonight was so fun doing it again! They had Karaoke in the next room so obviously we did that. On mine and Matthew’s third date he took me to karaoke night and sang “Man, I Feel Like a Woman” and I think I fell in love with him right there. All 6”5 of his manly self belting out Shania. So I sang it tonight in honor of him (i gave you a little treat at the end of this reel 🤪😂) I know he was with us tonight, and I’d be willing to bet he was jealous he couldn’t get up there with me. Get out of ya comfort zone and do something different, friends. It helps tend to whatever ails you.

This was such a fun mural for me to work on. Particularly since @megmatterstx supported this project and her butterfly is prominently featured here. Y’all know I am a safe place to discuss mental health, and it brings me so much joy that I was able to contribute to the cause.

Went thrifting with my sisters today! I don’t usually pick up anything for myself, I love to go just to be with them. But I also love to admire all the things, and I think about the life they lived before I met them. I’m calling this little reel “things I think are cutie cute but you think are creepy 😜”

I’d been eyeing this amaziiiiing vase all year and my parents gifted it to me for Christmas! But that gold is OFFENSIVE 💥💥 so I’m toning it down. I’m using Rub N Buff in Antique gold. I’m just applying it with a disposable glove and my finger! I’m going to let it set, then I’ll buff it out a little, and she will be the muted queen I’m wanting.

Let’s get prepped to paint in my little makeshift studio. The most important part before I start any project is always the foundation. Quality paint, artist grade brushes, brush sizes, a cutie mug to clean my brushes, finishing pens, even putting on Netflix is included in that. With out the proper foundation or prep work, things rarely go smoothly for me. And that’s actually true in all facets of my life!

I’ve been wanting to try this ever since I saw this new cake  trend like, four years ago. I learned a lot and thought this was such a fun, freeing little project! I thought the vibe and the message were perfect for Valentine’s season, and Miley’s new bop natch was the perfect fit.
Hot tip: if you’re a creative and you feel stuck in a rut, do something you’ve been wanting to try, or attempt to teach yourself a new skill. It’ll pop you right out of that rut, I promise! It’s a great brain excercize.

Let’s do a Paintbrush Edit. 
.
.
I have collected so many different brands, types, and styles of paintbrushes over the years so I decided it was time to edit them down. I felt the bristles of each brush and then put them in four categories: trash, mural painting, Scout’s brushes, brushes that can be for any use - but I’m mostly thinking about the kiddos I do projects with. (My personal brushes have their own special cedar drawer to keep them safe, clean, and tidy) I love a good declutter and organizing sesh. It’s like getting a head massage for me 🫠🤘🏽
I cannoooooot 🫶🏽🫶🏽🫶🏽🫶🏽🤩

This is your reminder to teach your daughters how to check their tire pressure and how to fill it. You never know where life will take them, and these basic skills my dad taught me have made my adult life much less difficult as far as daily living goes. Today I could tell my car wasn’t driving like it normally does, and sure enough my tire pressure was down to TEN PSI - anything below 20 is considered a flat tire 🥵🫥. Yikes!

Watch a Dallas Stars game from my POV! I’ve never been a huge sports enthusiast but I AM an experience enthusiast lol. My fam had a few season tickets to the Stars when I was in high school and my brother played all the way up to college hockey, so the love for the sport is sort of inherent for me. We got my dad tickets for his birthday and we all went to celebrate last night. This POV and sound is totally accurately showing you what’s going on in my little peabrain. I of course love watching the game, but i also like to decode the player’s lives. Are they married, are they nice, who’s the favorite on the team. I like to watch all the people around me and see how each person enjoys the game differently.  There was i THINK a first date going on in front of me, and that was fun to watch 😹. I even took a few laps to explore the four levels at the American Airlines Center. I totally recommend going at least once in your lifetime! #eatprayloveera

SATURDAY FEB 11: I am doing FREE watercolor Croquis style sketches at the DALLAS FARMERS MARKET from 11-2. I’ll be at the Shed’s entry. Each sketch takes 5-8 minutes so spots are for sure limited, and it’s first come, first serve. The DFM is doing a wine tasting event too so make sure you come ready for the cutest pre-valentine activity!

Up next in my EatPrayLove Era: Go to a concert alone. And it was my all time favorite, Death Cab for Cutie. I’m a huge music person (appreciation only 🫠) &DCFC has just been in the background in all the stages of my life since 2004. He played “I Will Follow You Into the Dark” & I sobbed my little heart out. I love that track so much, that I adjusted the lyrics a bit and it became one of the lullabies I sang Scouty. 
.
.
Going to a show like that was a really interesting experience. I’ve gone to concerts alone before but this time, purposefully alone, was something else. I posted up near the front side of the stage and vibed for 3 hours. I will tell you that I am NOT young any more &I really wished I had like, a camping chair with me 🤌🏼🤌🏼, because the venue was basically standing GA only. I’m such an old lady that I gave up my primo spot to go to the very back to stretch my back out on the hand railing to the stairs. Lol But I was in good company because there were a few other 30 somethings with the same idea 😭. Do you love how WRECKED I look at the end of this reel? My body was soooo mad at me when I woke up
.
I’ve always enjoyed my own company and liked doing things by myself, but doing these eatpraylove things are actually kind of hard since they’re not passive and done with intent. I will tell you I am growing a lot, rewiring my brain, reteaching myself how to truly enjoy things with out having to have my best friend and husband with me. I don’t like it. There was a couple in front of me, standing with each other like we probably would have and that made me really sad, but that’s part of being introspective. Feeling all the things. Good and bad. And really sitting in it.
.
There were 4200 people packed in there and wouldn’t you know it, @lindsayplacke my friend of almost 10 years was there with her husband, literally right next to me! I saw her unmistakeable profile and grabbed her elbow and squeezed her tight!That was so fun.&even though I enjoyed the show in my little spot alone, it felt nice knowing someone I care about was there too. 
.
I wonder if I should start tellin y’all locals when I’m going to go do something and we can do this together.

Starting my Valentine’s Day by putting Matthew’s ashes into a keepsake locket. Miss you every second of every day, Lumberjack. I wish you were coming with me today. ##PS - that is a look of slight disgust because…you know…it’s kinda gross. Lol. Another PS: I didn’t call Alfie over to sit with me. He just did. So grateful for companion animals that know when we need them.  Footnote: Matthew usually rides around shotgun in my car, sometimes in the backseat. 🤷🏼‍♀️ idk. Grief. Makes you so weird things

You know how all these years I’ve posted on Valentine’s Day something in the realm of “Happy Love day. I hope you all had something fluffy to snuggle with today” - well today I’m extra grateful for my little buddy. I hope all y’all truly had a lovely day, and if it wasn’t a lovely day thats okay too. You can come here and tell me about it and I’ll listen.

Today was the first Valentines Day in my entire existence that I’ve felt sad. But i decided I’m just owning that with no excuses, no silver lining to share this time, im just allowing it to be what it is. Feeling this way surprised me because y’all know I’ve never put a lot of weight on holidays. This is an indicator to me that I need to put some more work in. Crying is pretty unusual for me, especially unprovoked crying. .
Now that THAT is out of the way let me tell you a story. Matthew always bought gas gokart races in packs so he could always invite friends and they wouldn’t have to pay for anything. I’d say it was one of his fav things. He’d take me out to the track and teach me how to drive because he wanted me to “smoke all the boys”. He always wanted to parade me around like that. 😏 I called the Karting place yesterday to see if maybe he had any races left in his account. I told her kind of why I was thinking about coming out there to do a race and briefly about Matthew… he didn’t have an extra race but she said “you know, I have an extra one on my account. Let me transfer it.” 🥹 precious angel, named Randy. Sweet thing. I met her today and she gave me a big hug. People are just so good, you know? She said “im sorry I’ve just never lost anyone before so I don’t know what to say” and I told her that’s normal and most people don’t, and it’s really okay! So she hugged me. And I’ll never tire of that kind of thing.
.
.
I brought his ashes with me. His parents and siblings brought his ashes to the track this time-ish last year and I felt like it was the perfect thing to do today. I did the one race she gave me. She printed all his racing records for me to admire. I also HATED that his name was “pectorals” for anytime he needed a nickname like at the bowling alley, Nintendo avatar, etc. lol I thought it was so cringey. I mean I get it, it’s a play on his last name and his hot bod but still. No sir 🙅‍♀️🙅‍♀️🙅‍♀️. He thought that was the funniest thing. #eatprayloveera

I made you a little solo-date ASMR vid. I took myself out tonight to the candlelit  string quartet honoring Adele and the experience was 10/10. I was stuck in dallas traffic even though I left two hours early, and I missed the performance I paid for. The company basically told me sorry Charlie no refunds no excuses. So the beginning of this you see me frustrated, at a rooftop restaurant I’d been wanting to check out, trying to problem solve. Thankfully they let me transfer the ticket last second! It was such a cool experience and vibe. I’m such a sucker for anything candle lit and moody. I closed my eyes for half the show and definitely cried twice too? What?? Music does that to me though. I love that music can effect the human soul so deeply. (Especially with Adele!) I sat next to these cutie Brazilians that kept telling me how gorg I was and that I could be Adele’s sister ☠️😆😆. That’s another reason why I love doing these EatPrayLove things - it forces me to totally be outside of my comfy self and I get to meet the funnest people. 🫶🏽#eatprayloveera

social_posts.post_text:
“Collective effervescence is the feeling of energy and harmony when people are engaged in a shared purpose. It is a joie de vivre that manifests when we share moments with others, such as being in a stadium that erupts in simultaneous applause when a musician returns for an encore performance.” 
.
.
Except have you felt this on a small scale? It’s actually so magical. I didn’t know there was a coined term for this until i heard about it the other day. I love it! In the last year of my life I’ve felt this very feeling so many times, and I’m extra sensitive to it. I just love when people get together and can just be happy, you know? It’s beautiful.
This is something I’ve learned in the last 3 years, but this last year specifically. What’s the point of going through hard things if you don’t use it for good, growth, and gratitude?

The first day of my new life. My cute 900 sq/ft place in Downtown Dallas - y’all know I couldn’t ask for more right now. Can’t wait to share all the new adventures.

This episode in my #EatPrayLoveEra - 👑 @heatherkmcmahan ‘s show, stag, literally front row breaking my neck to giggle in the best way. This is my second time going (remember when i drove all the way to Austin a few years ago?) and she had me in literal tears at one point. I also need you to know the dress code to her shows is mixed animal print and sequins. 😌

Scout and I went exploring on the Katy Trail this morning. It’s just a few steps from my place and it’s one of the reasons I chose this place to live. So lovely. Last night I showed her my #eatprayloveera hashtag. She was a little confused on why I’m doing all these things by myself. I explained to her about the book Eat Pray Love. How the author lived through some trauma and decided to go across the world to eat, pray, and love her way through her heartache until she didn’t feel it anymore. I told Scout I am sort of doing that. Because I wanted to remember I love myself after all the hurt I’ve been through… because if you don’t love yourself, how can you expect to really love someone else? It’s so important to be able to be by yourself, learn to love the world around you, and find joy in your own mind. I really didn’t think about the fact that Scout is watching how I’m handing life, and after that conversation with her I felt checked - definitely refocused myself. 🫶🏽
Y’all better get out of the house and go play at the park with your kids. Not go WITH them. PLAY WITH them. Your inner child will thank you for the healing sesh.
One thing about me is I am NOT a camping girlie. But I will find a way to have a good attitude in the name of a good time. Watch me force myself to be happy about putting a tent together 🫠🫠🫠🫠
Let’s break down our campsite. Also with a good attitude 😛
First Annual Coslett Campout in Papas 100 Acre Woods.

On this episode of #eatprayloveera - don’t sleep on the jazz club. I went to one down the way from me to work on some digital art … And it ended up being such a fun experience that I want to go back every night until forever.  Apparently this place is where local jazz legends frequent every night. I left this joint a totally different person with 3x more friends than I began with. My soul is full and I have so much respect for these artists just laying it all out there in the name of jazz and slam poetry … my newest bucket list item - get the guts to perform my own spoken word. I’ve got a lot to say but I don’t want anyone to hear it. 🤪 anyway - do yourself a favor and find your nearest open mic jazz night. Your entire soul will thank you.
Poor Alfie. It was time for his yearly buzz. But at least he can see now!
Work on this Mothers Day board with me. And can we talk about this band I just found that I put as the sound? @thespruceandhollow magical.

Mothers Day Boards Part II. ***let’s go ahead and ignore that i spelled bouquet wrong. I’m going back to fix it**** What you don’t see here is my friend @nikkismithdesigns stopping to chat about her windows I’m painting this weekend - and she told me she loved seeing that I was smiling while I was chalkin’ with my headphones on. I didn’t even realize it. If you would have told me this time last year that I’d be cheesin’ while I was working instead of suppressing big fatty crocodile tears, I would have totally called you a liar. So grateful.

The first time I heard this was right after matthew passed and I hated it so much. I can’t really explain why, but I hated it. Probably because I wanted the love i have to be going to him and anything else was unacceptable. But since I’ve shifted the podcasts I listen to for this season of life I’m in, I’ve actually heard it a lot from a lot of different, wise people. Idk if it’s the Baader–Meinhof phenomenon or not but I’m good with this thought now. In fact I whole heartedly accept it and agree with it and I think is such a beautiful way to look at processing tragedy and loss. It’s the perfect way to describe what I was going through, and why my skin felt like I was swimming in acid all day every day. Once I accepted this, my grief process started looking and feeling different. It’s amazing how powerful our little brains are and the power of our thoughts. #abdigitalart

One of my favorite things to do is experience different cultures and to learn about their uniqueness - and when spirituality is involved it makes it that much better. We visited a Buddhist temple because we thought their festival was still going on, but we missed it by a day. But I’m kind of glad we missed it because we had the whole place to ourselves and I got to chat with this Monk who lives there and showed us around. One of my lifelong bucket lists is to visit a monastery in the Himalayan mountains , did I ever tell you that?

A few things. 1.TS is the cure to any mental ailment. 2. Scout had to fight her secondhand embarrassment with me in the theater tonight 3. Letting loose and singscreaming off the top of your lungs with your favorite humans is a top tier life experience.

I spent the last moments of the most beautiful year of 2023 with my favorite people: the fam. We played games, everyone brought so much food it made thanksgiving look like an appetizer situation, fireworks, giggles, crafting and my favorite… lounging. Lounging in my moms amazing closet and bathroom with my niece, mom and daughter (and puppy) trying on MayMay’s hair products, makeup, all the things. Scout was in serious heaven. 2023 was a year of growth, learning, huge love, and stability for me. I’m not sure 2024 can top this sustainable and comforting time in my life but one can hope. Cheers, friends. And thank you for all your love and support over the years - I would never be here if it wasn’t for you. Xoxo
